<p class="EnTeteTranscription">Jones, John. Letter to Judge Adam Mabane, 1787, with a copy of Jones's testimony 1783. An electronic transcription. MFTP #0003</p><div class="ContenuPage">
<p><span class="fw">2</span>
</p>
<p style="text-align:justify;">against a most unjustifiable Act of the Defendant M<sup>r</sup> Cochrane;</p>
<p style="text-align:justify;">That this being the only matter <span class="AddHand-author">to </span>which my Evidence (on the special Interrogatory) refers, I have been guilty of <span style="text-decoration:underline;">Temrity</span> <span class="AddHand-editors">[ed.n.: temerity]</span> &amp; <span style="text-decoration:underline;">Untruth</span> in asserting that the Counsel for M<sup>r</sup> Cochrane was refused to be heard, whose written answer, as <span style="text-decoration:underline;">read</span> &amp; <span style="text-decoration:underline;">filed</span>, signed both my M<sup>r</sup> Cochrane &amp; his Counsel, <span style="text-decoration:underline;">Remains</span> <span style="text-decoration:underline;">on</span> <span style="text-decoration:underline;">Record</span>. <span class="DelHand-author">Now, Sir I</span></p>
<p style="text-align:justify;"><span class="AddHand-author">Now, Sir, I</span> do once more in the face of the world declare, that what I gave in testimony, &amp; what I have more briefly stated in this Letter I did hear and see done and said by <span class="DelHand-author">you</span> <span class="AddHand-author"><span style="text-decoration:underline;">YOU</span></span> in the Court of Common Pleas; and I shall now proceed to prove that you have knowingly, &amp; deliberately misrepresented facts, and that you were affraid of bringing Oral testimony to confront mine, because you knew that every Iota of my evidence would be confirmed by your own Witnesses.</p>
<p style="text-align:justify;">In your Comments you refer to the Records of the Court, to prove that you did not give Judgement on M<sup>r </sup>Williams's Motion before M<sup>r</sup> Panets written Paper was <span style="text-decoration:underline;">read</span> and <span style="text-decoration:underline;">filed</span>; and this you do with as much confidence as if you believed that the World would receive them as the most authentic Evidence, whereas it is generally understood that they carry very little weight with them from the Circumstance, as represented on the investigation, that some are lost, some are blotted.</p>
<p style="text-align:justify;">JJ</p>
<p style="text-align:right;">and</p>

<p align="page-number"><span class="AddHand-editors">[5]</span></p>

